<inglise> Directive 2000/31/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu direktiiv 2000/31/E&Uuml; </eesti>
<inglise> on certain legal aspects of information society services, in particular electronic commerce, in the Internal Market (Directive on electronic commerce) </inglise>
<eesti> info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste teatavate &otilde;iguslike aspektide, eriti elektroonilise kaubanduse kohta siseturul (Direktiiv elektroonilise kaubanduse kohta) </eesti>
<inglise> of 8 June 2000 </inglise>
<eesti> 8. juuni 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT AND THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA PARLAMENT JA EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Articles 47(2), 55 and 95 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 47 l&otilde;iget 2 ning artikleid 55 ja 95, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Acting in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 251 of the Treaty(3), </inglise>
<eesti> vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklis 251 s&auml;testatud menetlusele (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The European Union is seeking to forge ever closer links between the States and peoples of Europe, to ensure economic and social progress; in accordance with Article 14(2) of the Treaty, the internal market comprises an area without internal frontiers in which the free movements of goods, services and the freedom of establishment are ensured; the development of information society services within the area without internal frontiers is vital to eliminating the barriers which divide the European peoples. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) Euroopa Liit p&uuml;&uuml;ab rajada veelgi l&auml;hemaid sidemeid Euroopa riikide ja rahvaste vahel, et tagada majanduslikku ja &uuml;hiskondlikku arengut; vastavalt asutamislepingu artikli 14 l&otilde;ikele 2 kujutab siseturg endast sisepiirideta ala, kus on tagatud kaupade ja teenuste vaba liikumine ning asutamisvabadus; info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste arendamine sel sisepiirideta alal on Euroopa rahvaid lahutavate t&otilde;kete k&otilde;rvaldamiseks oluline. </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The development of electronic commerce within the information society offers significant employment opportunities in the Community, particularly in small and medium-sized enterprises, and will stimulate economic growth and investment in innovation by European companies, and can also enhance the competitiveness of European industry, provided that everyone has access to the Internet. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) Elektroonilise kaubanduse arendamine info&uuml;hiskonnas annab &uuml;henduses m&auml;rkimisv&auml;&auml;rseid t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imalusi, eriti v&auml;ikestele ja keskmise suurusega ettev&otilde;tetele, ergutab Euroopa ettev&otilde;tete majanduslikku kasvu ja investeeringuid uuendustesse ning v&otilde;ib samuti suurendada Euroopa t&ouml;&ouml;stuse konkurentsiv&otilde;imet juhul, kui k&otilde;igil on juurdep&auml;&auml;s Internetile. </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Community law and the characteristics of the Community legal order are a vital asset to enable European citizens and operators to take full advantage, without consideration of borders, of the opportunities afforded by electronic commerce; this Directive therefore has the purpose of ensuring a high level of Community legal integration in order to establish a real area without internal borders for information society services. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) &Uuml;henduse &otilde;igus ja &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguskorra iseloom on oluline eelis, mis v&otilde;imaldab Euroopa kodanikel ja ettev&otilde;tetel piire arvestamata t&auml;ielikult kasutada k&otilde;iki elektroonilise kaubanduse poolt pakutavaid v&otilde;imalusi; seet&otilde;ttu on k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk tagada &uuml;henduse k&otilde;rgetasemeline &otilde;iguslik integratsioon, et kehtestada info&uuml;hiskonna teenustele tegelik sisepiirideta ala. </eesti>
<inglise> (4) It is important to ensure that electronic commerce could fully benefit from the internal market and therefore that, as with Council Directive 89/552/EEC of 3 October 1989 on the coordination of certain provisions laid down by law, regulation or administrative action in Member States concerning the pursuit of television broadcasting activities(4), a high level of Community integration is achieved. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) T&auml;htis on tagada, et elektrooniline kaubandus saaks t&auml;ielikult kasutada siseturgu, ja seet&otilde;ttu tuleb &uuml;henduses saavutada samasugune integratsiooni k&otilde;rge tase, nagu on saavutatud n&otilde;ukogu 3. oktoobri 1989. aasta direktiiviga 89/552/EM&Uuml; liikmesriikide teleringh&auml;&auml;lingutegevust k&auml;sitlevate teatavate &otilde;igusnormide koosk&otilde;lastamise kohta. (4) </eesti>
<inglise> (5) The development of information society services within the Community is hampered by a number of legal obstacles to the proper functioning of the internal market which make less attractive the exercise of the freedom of establishment and the freedom to provide services; these obstacles arise from divergences in legislation and from the legal uncertainty as to which national rules apply to such services; in the absence of coordination and adjustment of legislation in the relevant areas, obstacles might be justified in the light of the case-law of the Court of Justice of the European Communities; legal uncertainty exists with regard to the extent to which Member States may control services originating from another Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) Info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste arengut &uuml;henduses takistavad mitmed siseturu n&otilde;uetekohase toimimise &otilde;iguslikud t&otilde;kked, mis muudavad asutamisvabaduse ja teenuste osutamise vabaduse kasutamise v&auml;hem ligit&otilde;mbavaks; need t&otilde;kked tekivad &otilde;igusaktide lahknevustest ja selliste teenuste suhtes kohaldatavate siseriiklike eeskirjade &otilde;iguskindlusetusest; kui asjakohaste valdkondade &otilde;igusaktid on koosk&otilde;lastamata ja kohandamata, v&otilde;ib t&otilde;kkeid &otilde;igustada Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Kohtu pretsedendi&otilde;igust silmas pidades; &otilde;iguskindlusetust esineb sellises ulatuses, milles liikmesriik v&otilde;ib kontrollida teisest liikmesriigist p&auml;rit teenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise> (6) In the light of Community objectives, of Articles 43 and 49 of the Treaty and of secondary Community law, these obstacles should be eliminated by coordinating certain national laws and by clarifying certain legal concepts at Community level to the extent necessary for the proper functioning of the internal market; by dealing only with certain specific matters which give rise to problems for the internal market, this Directive is fully consistent with the need to respect the principle of subsidiarity as set out in Article 5 of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Pidades silmas &uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artiklite 43 ja 49 ning teiseste &otilde;igusaktide eesm&auml;rki, tuleks need t&otilde;kked k&otilde;rvaldada teatavate siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide koosk&otilde;lastamise ja teatavate &uuml;henduse tasandi &otilde;iguslike printsiipide t&auml;psustamise teel sel m&auml;&auml;ral, mis on vajalik siseturu n&otilde;uetekohaseks toimimiseks; k&auml;sitledes ainult teatavaid konkreetseid siseturul probleeme tekitavad k&uuml;simusi, j&auml;rgib k&auml;esolev direktiiv t&auml;ielikult asutamislepingu artiklis 5 etten&auml;htud subsidiaarsusp&otilde;him&otilde;tte respekteerimise vajadust. </eesti>
<inglise> (7) In order to ensure legal certainty and consumer confidence, this Directive must lay down a clear and general framework to cover certain legal aspects of electronic commerce in the internal market. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) &Otilde;iguskindluse ja tarbijate usalduse tagamiseks peab k&auml;esolev direktiiv s&auml;testama selge ja &uuml;ldise raamistiku, mis h&otilde;lmaks siseturu elektroonilise kaubanduse teatavaid &otilde;iguslikke aspekte. </eesti>
<inglise> (8) The objective of this Directive is to create a legal framework to ensure the free movement of information society services between Member States and not to harmonise the field of criminal law as such. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on luua &otilde;iguslik raamistik, mis tagaks info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste vaba liikumise liikmesriikide vahel, mitte &uuml;htlustada kriminaal&otilde;iguse valdkonda kui sellist. </eesti>
<inglise> (9) The free movement of information society services can in many cases be a specific reflection in Community law of a more general principle, namely freedom of expression as enshrined in Article 10(1) of the Convention for the Protection of Human Rights and Fundamental Freedoms, which has been ratified by all the Member States; for this reason, directives covering the supply of information society services must ensure that this activity may be engaged in freely in the light of that Article, subject only to the restrictions laid down in paragraph 2 of that Article and in Article 46(1) of the Treaty; this Directive is not intended to affect national fundamental rules and principles relating to freedom of expression. </inglise>
<eesti> 9) Info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste vaba liikumine v&otilde;ib paljudel juhtudel olla k&otilde;ikide liikmesriikide poolt ratifitseeritud inim&otilde;iguste ja p&otilde;hivabaduste kaitse konventsiooni artikli 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 sisalduva &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse &uuml;ldisema p&otilde;him&otilde;tte, nimelt s&otilde;navabaduse erivorm; seet&otilde;ttu peavad info&uuml;hiskonna teenustetarnet k&auml;sitlevad direktiivid tagama, et selle alaga nimetatud artikli t&auml;henduses v&otilde;ib tegelda vabalt, v&otilde;ttes arvesse ainult nimetatud artikli l&otilde;ikes 2 ja asutamislepingu artikli 46 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud piiranguid; k&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk pole m&otilde;jutada siseriiklikke s&otilde;navabadust k&auml;sitlevaid eeskirju ja p&otilde;him&otilde;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> (10) In accordance with the principle of proportionality, the measures provided for in this Directive are strictly limited to the minimum needed to achieve the objective of the proper functioning of the internal market; where action at Community level is necessary, and in order to guarantee an area which is truly without internal frontiers as far as electronic commerce is concerned, the Directive must ensure a high level of protection of objectives of general interest, in particular the protection of minors and human dignity, consumer protection and the protection of public health; according to Article 152 of the Treaty, the protection of public health is an essential component of other Community policies. </inglise>
<eesti> 10) Vastavalt proportsionaaluse p&otilde;him&otilde;ttele on k&auml;esolevas direktiivis etten&auml;htud meetmed rangelt piiratud miinimumiga, mida on vaja, et saavutada siseturu n&otilde;uetekohane toimimine; kui elektroonilise kaubanduse tegeliku sisepiirideta ala tagamiseks on vaja v&otilde;tta meetmeid &uuml;henduse tasandil, peab k&auml;esolev direktiiv kindlustama &uuml;ldiste huvide t&otilde;husa kaitse, eriti alaealiste kaitse ja inimv&auml;&auml;rikuse kaitse, tarbijakaitse ja rahva tervise kaitse; vastavalt asutamislepingu artiklile 152 on rahva tervise kaitse &uuml;henduse muu poliitika oluline koostisosa. </eesti>
<inglise> (11) This Directive is without prejudice to the level of protection for, in particular, public health and consumer interests, as established by Community acts; amongst others, Council Directive 93/13/EEC of 5 April 1993 on unfair terms in consumer contracts(5) and Directive 97/7/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 20 May 1997 on the protection of consumers in respect of distance contracts(6) form a vital element for protecting consumers in contractual matters; those Directives also apply in their entirety to information society services; that same Community acquis, which is fully applicable to information society services, also embraces in particular Council Directive 84/450/EEC of 10 September 1984 concerning misleading and comparative advertising(7), Council Directive 87/102/EEC of 22 December 1986 for the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States concerning consumer credit(8), Council Directive 93/22/EEC of 10 May 1993 on investment services in the securities field(9), Council Directive 90/314/EEC of 13 June 1990 on package travel, package holidays and package tours(10), Directive 98/6/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 16 February 1998 on consumer production in the indication of prices of products offered to consumers(11), Council Directive 92/59/EEC of 29 June 1992 on general product safety(12), Directive 94/47/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 26 October 1994 on the protection of purchasers in respect of certain aspects on contracts relating to the purchase of the right to use immovable properties on a timeshare basis(13), Directive 98/27/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 19 May 1998 on injunctions for the protection of consumers' interests(14), Council Directive 85/374/EEC of 25 July 1985 on the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions concerning liability for defective products(15), Directive 1999/44/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 25 May 1999 on certain aspects of the sale of consumer goods and associated guarantees(16), the future Directive of the European Parliament and of the Council concerning the distance marketing of consumer financial services and Council Directive 92/28/EEC of 31 March 1992 on the advertising of medicinal products(17); this Directive should be without prejudice to Directive 98/43/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 6 July 1998 on the approximation of the laws, regulations and administrative provisions of the Member States relating to the advertising and sponsorship of tobacco products(18) adopted within the framework of the internal market, or to directives on the protection of public health; this Directive complements information requirements established by the abovementioned Directives and in particular Directive 97/7/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> 11) K&auml;esolev direktiiv ei piira &uuml;henduse aktidega kehtestatud kaitse taset, eriti rahva tervise ja tarbija huvide kaitset; muu hulgas moodustavad n&otilde;ukogu 5. aprilli 1993. aasta direktiiv 93/13/EM&Uuml; eba&otilde;iglaste tingimuste kohta tarbijalepingutes (5) ning Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 20. mai 1997. aasta direktiiv 97/7/E&Uuml; tarbijakaitse kohta seoses sidevahendi abil s&otilde;lmitud lepingutega (6) olulise osa tarbijate kaitsmisel lepinguk&uuml;simustes; samuti kohaldatakse neid direktiive tervikuna info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste suhtes; seesama &uuml;henduse acquis, mida tervikuna kohaldatakse info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste suhtes, h&otilde;lmab eesk&auml;tt n&otilde;ukogu 10. septembri 1984. aasta direktiivi 84/450/EM&Uuml; eksitava ja v&otilde;rdleva reklaami kohta, (7) n&otilde;ukogu 22. detsembri 1986. aasta direktiivi 87/102/EM&Uuml; tarbijakrediiti k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (8) n&otilde;ukogu 10. mai 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/22/EM&Uuml; v&auml;&auml;rtpaberiturul pakutavate investeerimisteenuste kohta, (9) n&otilde;ukogu 13. juuni 1990. aasta direktiivi 90/314/EM&Uuml; reisipakettide, puhkusepakettide ja ekskursioonipakettide kohta, (10) Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 16. veebruari 1998. aasta direktiivi 98/6/E&Uuml; tarbijakaitse kohta tarbijatele pakutavate toodete hindade avaldamisel, (11) n&otilde;ukogu 29. juuni 1992. aasta direktiivi 92/59/EM&Uuml; toodete &uuml;ldise ohutuse kohta, (12) Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 26. oktoobri 1994. aasta direktiivi 94/47/E&Uuml; ostjate kaitse kohta, mis puudutab kinnisvara osaajalise kasutamise &otilde;iguse ostu-m&uuml;&uuml;gilepingute teatavaid aspekte, (13) Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 19. mai 1998. aasta direktiivi 98/27/E&Uuml; tarbijate huve kaitsvate ettekirjutuste kohta, (14) n&otilde;ukogu 25. juuli 1985. aasta direktiivi 85/374/EM&Uuml; liikmesriikide tootevastutust k&auml;sitlevate &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (15) Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 25. mai 1999. aasta direktiivi 1999/44/E&Uuml; tarbekaupade m&uuml;&uuml;gi teatavate aspektide ja nendega seotud garantiide kohta, (16) Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu tulevast direktiivi tarbijale suunatud finantsteenuste kaugturustuse kohta ning n&otilde;ukogu 31. m&auml;rtsi 1992. aasta direktiivi 92/28/EM&Uuml; ravimite reklaamimise kohta; (17) k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei tohiks piirata siseturuga seoses vastuv&otilde;etud Euroopa parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 6. juuli 1998. aasta direktiivi 98/43/E&Uuml; tubakatoodete reklaami ja sponsorlust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusnormide &uuml;htlustamise kohta (18) ega direktiive rahva tervise kaitse kohta; k&auml;esolev direktiiv t&auml;iendab eespool nimetatud direktiivides ja eriti direktiivis 97/7/E&Uuml; kehtestatud teaben&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise> (12) It is necessary to exclude certain activities from the scope of this Directive, on the grounds that the freedom to provide services in these fields cannot, at this stage, be guaranteed under the Treaty or existing secondary legislation; excluding these activities does not preclude any instruments which might prove necessary for the proper functioning of the internal market; taxation, particularly value added tax imposed on a large number of the services covered by this Directive, must be excluded form the scope of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> 12) K&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendusalast tuleb teatavad tegevusalad v&auml;lja j&auml;tta, sest praegusel etapil ei saa nendes valdkondades asutamislepingu v&otilde;i olemasolevate teiseste &otilde;igusaktidega tagada teenuste osutamise vabadust; nende tegevusalade v&auml;ljaj&auml;tmine ei v&auml;lista &uuml;htki vahendit, mis v&otilde;ib siseturu n&otilde;uetekohaseks toimimiseks osutuda vajalikuks; maksustamine, eriti suurelt hulgalt k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud teenustelt n&otilde;utav k&auml;ibemaks, tuleb k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalast v&auml;lja j&auml;tta. </eesti>
<inglise> (13) This Directive does not aim to establish rules on fiscal obligations nor does it pre-empt the drawing up of Community instruments concerning fiscal aspects of electronic commerce. </inglise>
<eesti> 13) K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk ei ole maksukohustusi reguleerivate eeskirjade kehtestamine, samuti ei v&auml;lista see elektroonilise kaubanduse maksustamist k&auml;sitlevate &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide koostamist. </eesti>
<inglise> (14) The protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data is solely governed by Directive 95/46/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 24 October 1995 on the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal data and on the free movement of such data(19) and Directive 97/66/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 15 December 1997 concerning the processing of personal data and the protection of privacy in the telecommunications sector(20) which are fully applicable to information society services; these Directives already establish a Community legal framework in the field of personal data and therefore it is not necessary to cover this issue in this Directive in order to ensure the smooth functioning of the internal market, in particular the free movement of personal data between Member States; the implementation and application of this Directive should be made in full compliance with the principles relating to the protection of personal data, in particular as regards unsolicited commercial communication and the liability of intermediaries; this Directive cannot prevent the anonymous use of open networks such as the Internet. </inglise>
<eesti> 14) &Uuml;ksikisikute kaitset isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel reguleerivad ainult Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 24. oktoobri 1995. aasta direktiiv 95/46/E&Uuml; &uuml;ksikisikute kaitse kohta isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisel ja selliste andmete vaba liikumise kohta (19) ning Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 15. detsembri 1997. aasta direktiiv 97/66/E&Uuml; isikuandmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ja eraelu kaitse kohta telekommunikatsioonisektoris, (20) mis on t&auml;ielikult kohaldatavad ka info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste suhtes; nende direktiividega on juba kehtestatud &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguslik raamistik isikuandmete alal ja seet&otilde;ttu ei ole siseturu n&otilde;uetekohase toimimise, eriti isikuandmete liikmesriikidevahelise vaba liikumise tagamiseks vaja seda k&uuml;simust k&auml;sitleda k&auml;esolevas direktiivis; k&auml;esoleva direktiivi rakendamine ja kohaldamine peaks toimuma t&auml;ielikus vastavuses isikuandmete kaitse p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega, eriti mis puudutab pealesunnitud kaubanduslikku teavet ja vahendajate vastutust; k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei saa t&otilde;kestada selliste avalike v&otilde;rkude nagu Internet anon&uuml;&uuml;mset kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise> (15) The confidentiality of communications is guaranteed by Article 5 Directive 97/66/EC; in accordance with that Directive, Member States must prohibit any kind of interception or surveillance of such communications by others than the senders and receivers, except when legally authorised. </inglise>
<eesti> 15) Teabevahetuse saladuse tagab direktiivi 97/66/E&Uuml; artikkel 5; vastavalt nimetatud direktiivile peavad liikmesriigid keelama saatja ja vastuv&otilde;tja vahelise teabevahetuse igasuguse pealtkuulamise v&otilde;i j&auml;litamise teiste poolt, v&auml;lja arvatud seadusega lubatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise> (16) The exclusion of gambling activities from the scope of application of this Directive covers only games of chance, lotteries and betting transactions, which involve wagering a stake with monetary value; this does not cover promotional competitions or games where the purpose is to encourage the sale of goods or services and where payments, if they arise, serve only to acquire the promoted goods or services. </inglise>
<eesti> 16) Hasartm&auml;ngude v&auml;ljaj&auml;tmine k&auml;esoleva direktiivi reguleerimisalast k&auml;ib ainult &otilde;nnem&auml;ngude, loteriide ja kihlvedude s&otilde;lmimiste kohta, kus tehakse rahalisi panuseid; see ei k&auml;i m&uuml;&uuml;giedendusv&otilde;istluste v&otilde;i m&auml;ngude kohta, mille eesm&auml;rk on kaupade v&otilde;i teenuste m&uuml;&uuml;gi edendamine ja mille maksed, kui neid tehakse, ainult aitavad omandada edendatavaid kaupu v&otilde;i teenuseid. </eesti>
<inglise> (17) The definition of information society services already exists in Community law in Directive 98/34/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 22 June 1998 laying down a procedure for the provision of information in the field of technical standards and regulations and of rules on information society services(21) and in Directive 98/84/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 20 November 1998 on the legal protection of services based on, or consisting of, conditional access(22); this definition covers any service normally provided for remuneration, at a distance, by means of electronic equipment for the processing (including digital compression) and storage of data, and at the individual request of a recipient of a service; those services referred to in the indicative list in Annex V to Directive 98/34/EC which do not imply data processing and storage are not covered by this definition. </inglise>
<eesti> 17) Info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste m&auml;&auml;ratlus &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktides on olemas juba Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 22. juuni 1998. aasta direktiivis 98/34/EM&Uuml;, milles on s&auml;testatud tehniliste standardite ja normide kohta k&auml;iva teabe ning info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste eeskirjade esitamise kord (21), ja Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 20. novembri 1998. aasta direktiivis 98/84/E&Uuml; tingimusjuurdep&auml;&auml;sul p&otilde;hinevate v&otilde;i seda sisaldavate teenuste &otilde;iguskaitse kohta; (22) see m&auml;&auml;ratlus h&otilde;lmab k&otilde;iki elektrooniliste andmet&ouml;&ouml;tlus- (kaasa arvatud digitaalne pakkimine) ja -salvestusseadmete abil eemalt ning teenuse saaja isikliku taotluse p&otilde;hjal osutatavaid teenuseid, mille eest tavaliselt makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu; direktiivi 98/34/E&Uuml; V lisa soovitusloendis nimetatud teenused, mis ei eelda andmet&ouml;&ouml;tlust ja -salvestust, ei kuulu k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ratluse alla. </eesti>
<inglise> (18) Information society services span a wide range of economic activities which take place on-line; these activities can, in particular, consist of selling goods on-line; activities such as the delivery of goods as such or the provision of services off-line are not covered; information society services are not solely restricted to services giving rise to on-line contracting but also, in so far as they represent an economic activity, extend to services which are not remunerated by those who receive them, such as those offering on-line information or commercial communications, or those providing tools allowing for search, access and retrieval of data; information society services also include services consisting of the transmission of information via a communication network, in providing access to a communication network or in hosting information provided by a recipient of the service; television broadcasting within the meaning of Directive EEC/89/552 and radio broadcasting are not information society services because they are not provided at individual request; by contrast, services which are transmitted point to point, such as video-on-demand or the provision of commercial communications by electronic mail are information society services; the use of electronic mail or equivalent individual communications for instance by natural persons acting outside their trade, business or profession including their use for the conclusion of contracts between such persons is not an information society service; the contractual relationship between an employee and his employer is not an information society service; activities which by their very nature cannot be carried out at a distance and by electronic means, such as the statutory auditing of company accounts or medical advice requiring the physical examination of a patient are not information society services. </inglise>
<eesti> 18) Paljud info&uuml;hiskonna teenused on seotud on-line toimuva majandustegevusega; eesk&auml;tt v&otilde;ib see seisneda kaupade on-line m&uuml;&uuml;gis; siia ei kuulu sellised tegevused nagu kaupade kui selliste tarnimine v&otilde;i teenuste osutamine off-line; info&uuml;hiskonna teenused ei piirdu ainult nende teenustega, mis on seotud on-line tehtud lepingutega, vaid laienevad, niiv&otilde;rd kuiv&otilde;rd need kujutavad endast majandustegevust, ka teenustele, mille eest nende saajad ei maksa, nagu n&auml;iteks teenused, mis pakuvad on-line infot v&otilde;i kaubanduslikku teavet v&otilde;i vahendeid, mis v&otilde;imaldavad andmete otsimist, neile ligip&auml;&auml;su ja v&auml;ljav&otilde;tteid neist; info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste hulka kuuluvad ka teenused, mis seisnevad teabe edastamises sidev&otilde;rgu kaudu, sidev&otilde;rgule juurdep&auml;&auml;su pakkumises v&otilde;i teenuse saaja antud teabe talletamises; teleringh&auml;&auml;ling direktiivi EM&Uuml;/89/552 t&auml;henduses ja raadioringh&auml;&auml;ling ei ole info&uuml;hiskonna teenused, sest neid ei osutata isikliku taotluse alusel; seevastu teenused, mida edastatakse punktist punkti, nagu tellitav videoteenus v&otilde;i kaubandusliku teabe pakkumine elektronposti teel, on info&uuml;hiskonna teenused; elektronposti v&otilde;i samav&auml;&auml;rsete isiklike sidevahendite kasutamine v&auml;ljaspool oma ametit, &auml;ri v&otilde;i elukutset tegutsevate f&uuml;&uuml;siliste isikute poolt, kaasa arvatud nende vahendite kasutamine kokkulepete s&otilde;lmimiseks selliste isikute vahel, ei ole info&uuml;hiskonna teenus; lepinguline suhe t&ouml;&ouml;taja ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja vahel pole info&uuml;hiskonna teenus; tegevused, mida juba nende olemuse t&otilde;ttu ei saa teha eemalt ja elektrooniliste vahenditega, nagu &auml;ri&uuml;hingute raamatupidamise p&otilde;hikirjaj&auml;rgne auditeerimine v&otilde;i patsiendi l&auml;bivaatust n&otilde;udev arstlik n&otilde;uanne ei ole info&uuml;hiskonna teenused. </eesti>
<inglise> (19) The place at which a service provider is established should be determined in conformity with the case-law of the Court of Justice according to which the concept of establishment involves the actual pursuit of an economic activity through a fixed establishment for an indefinite period; this requirement is also fulfilled where a company is constituted for a given period; the place of establishment of a company providing services via an Internet website is not the place at which the technology supporting its website is located or the place at which its website is accessible but the place where it pursues its economic activity; in cases where a provider has several places of establishment it is important to determine from which place of establishment the service concerned is provided; in cases where it is difficult to determine from which of several places of establishment a given service is provided, this is the place where the provider has the centre of his activities relating to this particular service. </inglise>
<eesti> 19) Teenuse osutaja asukoht tuleks m&auml;&auml;rata vastavalt Euroopa Kohtu pretsedendi&otilde;igusele, mille kohaselt asukohana m&otilde;istetakse majandustegevuse tegeliku teostamise p&uuml;siasukohta m&auml;&auml;ramata ajavahemiku jooksul; samuti on see n&otilde;ue t&auml;idetud, kui &auml;ri&uuml;hing on moodustatud konkreetseks ajavahemikuks; Interneti v&otilde;rgulehek&uuml;lje kaudu teenuseid osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu asukoht ei ole seal, kus asub v&otilde;rgulehek&uuml;lge toetav tehnika, v&otilde;i seal, kus on juurdep&auml;&auml;s sellele v&otilde;rgulehek&uuml;ljele, vaid see koht, kus ta teostab oma majandustegevust; juhtudel, kui teenuste osutajal on mitu asukohta, on t&auml;htis kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata, millisest asukohast osutatakse k&otilde;nelaust teenust; kui mitme asukoha t&otilde;ttu on raske kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata, millisest asukohast konkreetset teenust osutatakse, on selleks koht, kus teenuse osutajal on selle konkreetse teenusega tegelemise keskus. </eesti>
<inglise> (20) The definition of "recipient of a service" covers all types of usage of information society services, both by persons who provide information on open networks such as the Internet and by persons who seek information on the Internet for private or professional reasons. </inglise>
<eesti> 20) Teenuse saaja m&auml;&auml;ratlus h&otilde;lmab k&otilde;iki info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste kasutamise viise, nii nende isikute tegevust, kes osutavad teavet avatud v&otilde;rkudes nagu Internet, kui ka nende isikute tegevust, kes isiklikel v&otilde;i ametialastel p&otilde;hjustel Internetist teavet otsivad. </eesti>
<inglise> (21) The scope of the coordinated field is without prejudice to future Community harmonisation relating to information society services and to future legislation adopted at national level in accordance with Community law; the coordinated field covers only requirements relating to on-line activities such as on-line information, on-line advertising, on-line shopping, on-line contracting and does not concern Member States' legal requirements relating to goods such as safety standards, labelling obligations, or liability for goods, or Member States' requirements relating to the delivery or the transport of goods, including the distribution of medicinal products; the coordinated field does not cover the exercise of rights of pre-emption by public authorities concerning certain goods such as works of art. </inglise>
<eesti> 21) Selle koosk&otilde;lastatud valdkonna reguleerimisala ei piira edaspidi info&uuml;hiskonna teenuseid k&auml;sitlevate &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamist ega edaspidi siseriiklikul tasandil koosk&otilde;las &uuml;henduse &otilde;igusaktidega vastuv&otilde;etavaid &otilde;igusakte; koosk&otilde;lastatud valdkond h&otilde;lmab ainult selliseid tegevusi internetis nagu on-line teave, on-line reklaam, on-line pakkumine, on-line lepingud, mitte liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktides kaupadele esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid, nagu ohutusnormid, m&auml;rgistamiskohustused v&otilde;i vastutus kaupade eest, samuti mitte liikmesriikide poolt kaupade tarnele v&otilde;i veole esitatavaid n&otilde;udeid, kaasa arvatud ravimite turustamine; koosk&otilde;lastatud valdkond ei h&otilde;lma ametiv&otilde;imude ostuees&otilde;iguse kasutamist teatavate kaupade, n&auml;iteks kunstiteoste ostmisel. </eesti>
<inglise> (22) Information society services should be supervised at the source of the activity, in order to ensure an effective protection of public interest objectives; to that end, it is necessary to ensure that the competent authority provides such protection not only for the citizens of its own country but for all Community citizens; in order to improve mutual trust between Member States, it is essential to state clearly this responsibility on the part of the Member State where the services originate; moreover, in order to effectively guarantee freedom to provide services and legal certainty for suppliers and recipients of services, such information society services should in principle be subject to the law of the Member State in which the service provider is established. </inglise>
<eesti> 22) Info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste j&auml;relevalve peaks toimuma tegevuse l&auml;htekohas, et kindlustada avalike huviobjektide t&otilde;hus kaitse; sel eesm&auml;rgil tuleb tagada, et p&auml;dev asutus ei kaitseks mitte ainult oma riigi kodanikke, vaid k&otilde;iki &uuml;henduse kodanikke; liikmesriikidevahelise usalduse parandamiseks on oluline selgelt s&otilde;nastada teenuste p&auml;ritoluliikmesriigi kohustused; lisaks peaksid sellised info&uuml;hiskonna teenused nii teenuste osutamise vabaduse kui ka teenuse osutajate ja saajate &otilde;iguskindluse t&otilde;husaks tagamiseks p&otilde;him&otilde;tteliselt s&otilde;ltuma selle liikmesriigi &otilde;igusest, kus on teenuse osutaja asukoht. </eesti>
<inglise> (23) This Directive neither aims to establish additional rules on private international law relating to conflicts of law nor does it deal with the jurisdiction of Courts; provisions of the applicable law designated by rules of private international law must not restrict the freedom to provide information society services as established in this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> 23) K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk ei ole seaduste vastuolusid k&auml;sitleva rahvusvahelise era&otilde;iguse t&auml;iendavate eeskirjade kehtestamine, samuti ei k&auml;sitle see kohtute p&auml;devust; rahvusvahelise era&otilde;iguse eeskirjadega m&auml;&auml;ratud kohaldatava seaduse s&auml;tted ei tohi piirata k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga kehtestatud info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste osutamise vabadust. </eesti>
<inglise> (24) In the context of this Directive, notwithstanding the rule on the control at source of information society services, it is legitimate under the conditions established in this Directive for Member States to take measures to restrict the free movement of information society services. </inglise>
<eesti> 24) Hoolimata eeskirjast, et j&auml;relevalve info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste &uuml;le peab toimuma pakkumiskohas, on liikmesriikidel k&auml;esoleva direktiivi kontekstis &otilde;igus direktiiviga etten&auml;htud tingimustel v&otilde;tta meetmeid info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste vaba liikumise piiramiseks. </eesti>
<inglise> (25) National courts, including civil courts, dealing with private law disputes can take measures to derogate from the freedom to provide information society services in conformity with conditions established in this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> 25) Era&otilde;iguslike vaidlustega tegelevad siseriiklikud kohtud, kaasa arvatud tsiviilkohtud, v&otilde;ivad koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esolevas direktiivis kehtestatud n&otilde;uetega v&otilde;tta meetmeid, mis lahknevad info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste osutamise vabadusest. </eesti>
<inglise> (26) Member States, in conformity with conditions established in this Directive, may apply their national rules on criminal law and criminal proceedings with a view to taking all investigative and other measures necessary for the detection and prosecution of criminal offences, without there being a need to notify such measures to the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> 26) Liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esolevas direktiivis kehtestatud tingimustega kohaldada oma siseriiklikke kriminaal&otilde;iguse ja kriminaalmenetluse norme, et v&otilde;tta k&otilde;ik uurimis- ja muud meetmed, mis on vajalikud kuritegude avastamiseks ja karistuste m&otilde;istmiseks, ilma et neist meetmetest oleks vaja komisjonile teatada. </eesti>
<inglise> (27) This Directive, together with the future Directive of the European Parliament and of the Council concerning the distance marketing of consumer financial services, contributes to the creating of a legal framework for the on-line provision of financial services; this Directive does not pre-empt future initiatives in the area of financial services in particular with regard to the harmonisation of rules of conduct in this field; the possibility for Member States, established in this Directive, under certain circumstances of restricting the freedom to provide information society services in order to protect consumers also covers measures in the area of financial services in particular measures aiming at protecting investors. </inglise>
<eesti> 27) K&auml;esolev direktiiv koos Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu edaspidise direktiiviga tarbijale suunatud finantsteenuste kaugturustuse kohta aitab luua &otilde;iguslikku raamistikku on-line finantsteenuste osutamiseks; k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei v&auml;lista edaspidiseid algatusi finantsteenuste valdkonnas, pidades eriti silmas selle valdkonna tegutsemiseeskirjade &uuml;htlustamist; k&auml;esolevas direktiivis kehtestatud liikmesriikide v&otilde;imalus teatavatel asjaoludel info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste osutamise vabadust tarbijate kaitseks piirata h&otilde;lmab ka meetmeid finantsteenuste valdkonnas, eriti meetmeid, mille eesm&auml;rk on investorite kaitse. </eesti>
<inglise> (28) The Member States' obligation not to subject access to the activity of an information society service provider to prior authorisation does not concern postal services covered by Directive 97/67/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 15 December 1997 on common rules for the development of the internal market of Community postal services and the improvement of quality of service(23) consisting of the physical delivery of a printed electronic mail message and does not affect voluntary accreditation systems, in particular for providers of electronic signature certification service. </inglise>
<eesti> 28) Liikmesriikide kohustus mitte muuta info&uuml;hiskonna teenuse osutaja tegevus s&otilde;ltuvaks eelnevast loast ei h&otilde;lma Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 15. detsembri 1997. aasta direktiiviga 97/67/E&Uuml; (&uuml;henduse postiteenuste siseturu arengu &uuml;histe eeskirjade ja teenuse kvaliteedi parandamise kohta (23)) reguleeritud postiteenuseid, mis seisnevad tr&uuml;kitud elektronposti s&otilde;numi f&uuml;&uuml;silises k&auml;ttetoimetamises, ega m&otilde;juta vabatahtlikke akrediteerimiss&uuml;steeme, eesk&auml;tt elektroonilise allkirja t&otilde;estamise teenust. </eesti>
<inglise> (29) Commercial communications are essential for the financing of information society services and for developing a wide variety of new, charge-free services; in the interests of consumer protection and fair trading, commercial communications, including discounts, promotional offers and promotional competitions or games, must meet a number of transparency requirements; these requirements are without prejudice to Directive 97/7/EC; this Directive should not affect existing Directives on commercial communications, in particular Directive 98/43/EC. </inglise>
<eesti> 29) Kaubanduslik teave on h&auml;davajalik info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste rahastamiseks ja laia valiku uute tasuta teenuste v&auml;ljaarendamiseks; tarbijakaitse ja ausa kauplemise huvides peab kaubanduslik teave, sealhulgas teave allahindluste, m&uuml;&uuml;giedenduspakkumiste ja m&uuml;&uuml;giedendusv&otilde;istluste v&otilde;i -m&auml;ngude kohta, vastama mitmetele selguse ja arusaadavuse n&otilde;uetele; need n&otilde;uded ei piira direktiivi 97/7/E&Uuml; kohaldamist; k&auml;esolev direktiiv ei peaks m&otilde;jutama olemasolevaid direktiive kaubandusliku teabe kohta, eriti direktiivi 98/43/E&Uuml;. </eesti>
<inglise> (30) The sending of unsolicited commercial communications by electronic mail may be undesirable for consumers and information society service providers and may disrupt the smooth functioning of interactive networks; the question of consent by recipient of certain forms of unsolicited commercial communications is not addressed by this Directive, but has already been addressed, in particular, by Directive 97/7/EC and by Directive 97/66/EC; in Member States which authorise unsolicited commercial communications by electronic mail, the setting up of appropriate industry filtering initiatives should be encouraged and facilitated; in addition it is necessary that in any event unsolicited commercial communities are clearly identifiable as such in order to improve transparency and to facilitate the functioning of such industry initiatives; unsolicited commercial communications by electronic mail should not result in additional communication costs for the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti> 30) Pealesunnitud kaubandusliku teabe saatmine elektronposti teel v&otilde;ib olla nii tarbijatele kui ka info&uuml;hiskonna teenuste osutajale soovimatu ning h&auml;irida interaktiivsete v&otilde;rkude ladusat toimimist; k&auml;esolevas direktiivis ei k&auml;sitleta teatavate pealesunnitud kaubandusliku teabe vormide saaja n&otilde;usoleku k&uuml;simust, seda on juba tehtud, eesk&auml;tt direktiivis 97/7/E&Uuml; ja direktiivis 97/66/E&Uuml;; liikmesriigid, kes lubavad pealesunnitud kaubandusliku teabe saatmist elektronposti teel, peaksid julgustama ja soodustada vastaval tegevusalal filtreerimisalgatusi; lisaks on vaja, et pealesunnitud kaubanduslik teave oleks igal juhul sellisena identifitseeritav, et parandada avatust ja t&otilde;hustada selle tegevusala algatuste toimet; pealesunnitud kaubanduslik teave elektronposti teel ei tohiks saajale kaasa tuua t&auml;iendavaid sidekulusid. </eesti>
<inglise> (31) Member States which allow the sending of unsolicited commercial communications by electronic mail without prior consent of the recipient by service providers established in their territory have to ensure that the service providers consult regularly and respect the opt-out registers in which natural persons not wishing to receive such commercial communications can register themselves. </inglise>
<eesti> 31) Liikmesriigid, kes lubavad, et nende territooriumil tegutsevad teenuse osutajad saadavad pealesunnitud kaubanduslikku teavet elektronposti teel saaja eelneva n&otilde;usolekuta, peavad tagama, et teenuse osutajad j&auml;lgivad korrap&auml;raselt loobujate registreid, kuhu v&otilde;ivad registreeruda f&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud, kes ei soovi sellist kaubanduslikku teavet saada, ja respekteerivad neid. </eesti>
<inglise> (32) In order to remove barriers to the development of cross-border services within the Community which members of the regulated professions might offer on the Internet, it is necessary that compliance be guaranteed at Community level with professional rules aiming, in particular, to protect consumers or public health; codes of conduct at Community level would be the best means of determining the rules on professional ethics applicable to commercial communication; the drawing-up or, where appropriate, the adaptation of such rules should be encouraged without prejudice to the autonomy of professional bodies and associations. </inglise>
<eesti> 32) Et k&otilde;rvaldada t&otilde;kked, mis &uuml;henduses takistavad nende piiri&uuml;leste teenuste v&auml;ljaarendamist, mida reguleeritud kutsealade esindajad v&otilde;ivad pakkuda Interneti kaudu, on vaja &uuml;henduse tasandil tagada vastavus kutsealaste eeskirjadega, mille eesm&auml;rk on eesk&auml;tt tarbijate v&otilde;i rahva tervise kaitse; tegevusjuhendid &uuml;henduse tasandil oleks parim vahend kaubandusliku teabe suhtes kohaldatava kutse-eetika eeskirjade m&auml;&auml;ratlemiseks; selliste eeskirjade koostamist v&otilde;i vajaduse korral mugandamist tuleks julgustada, piiramata kutseorganisatsioonide ja -&uuml;henduste autonoomiat. </eesti>
<inglise> (33) This Directive complements Community law and national law relating to regulated professions maintaining a coherent set of applicable rules in this field. </inglise>
<eesti> 33) K&auml;esolev direktiiv t&auml;iendab reguleeritud kutsealasid k&auml;sitlevat &uuml;henduse &otilde;igust ja siseriiklikku &otilde;igust, s&auml;ilitades seejuures valdkonnas kohaldatavate eeskirjade &uuml;htsuse. </eesti>
<inglise> (34) Each Member State is to amend its legislation containing requirements, and in particular requirements as to form, which are likely to curb the use of contracts by electronic means; the examination of the legislation requiring such adjustment should be systematic and should cover all the necessary stages and acts of the contractual process, including the filing of the contract; the result of this amendment should be to make contracts concluded electronically workable; the legal effect of electronic signatures is dealt with by Directive 1999/93/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 13 December 1999 on a Community framework for electronic signatures(24); the acknowledgement of receipt by a service provider may take the form of the on-line provision of the service paid for. </inglise>
<eesti> 34) K&otilde;ik liikmesriigid peavad muutma oma &otilde;igusakte, mis sisaldavad niisuguseid n&otilde;udeid vormi kohta, mis usutavasti v&otilde;ivad piirata elektrooniliste lepingute kasutamist; niisuguste kohandamist vajavate &otilde;igusaktide l&auml;bivaatamine peaks olema s&uuml;stemaatiline ja h&otilde;lmama k&otilde;ik lepingu s&otilde;lmimiseks vajalikud etapid ja toimingud, kaasa arvatud lepingu registreerimine; muudatuse tulemusel peaks olema v&otilde;imalik kasutada elektrooniliselt s&otilde;lmitud lepinguid; elektrooniliste allkirjade &otilde;iguslikku toimet k&auml;sitleb Euroopa Parlamendi ja n&otilde;ukogu 13. detsembri 1999. aasta direktiiv 1999/93/E&Uuml; elektrooniliste allkirjade &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohta &uuml;henduses; (24) teenuse osutaja vastuv&otilde;tuteatis v&otilde;ib v&otilde;tta tasulise on-line teenuse osutamise kuju. </eesti>
<inglise> (35) This Directive does not affect Member States' possibility of maintaining or establishing general or specific legal requirements for contracts which can be fulfilled by electronic means, in particular requirements concerning secure electronic signatures. </inglise>
