<inglise> Member States shall in particular ensure that the legal requirements applicable to the contractual process neither create obstacles for the use of electronic contracts nor result in such contracts being deprived of legal effectiveness and validity on account of their having been made by electronic means. </inglise>
<eesti> Eesk&auml;tt tagavad liikmesriigid, et lepingus&otilde;lmimise protsessi suhtes kohaldatavad &otilde;igusnormid ei takista elektrooniliste lepingute kasutamist ega p&otilde;hjusta selliste lepingute kehtetust selle t&otilde;ttu, et need on s&otilde;lmitud elektroonilisel teel. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may lay down that paragraph 1 shall not apply to all or certain contracts falling into one of the following categories: </inglise>
